HEADWORD: Abactinal
<hw>Ab*ac"ti*nal</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧b*⟦acr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧*n⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ab</ets> + E. <ets>actinal</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the surface or end opposite to the
mouth in a radiate animal; -- opposed to <contr>actinal</contr>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The aboral or <xex>abactinal</xex> area.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>L.
Agassiz.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
